The paper deals with the problem of dynamic optimality for binary search trees, which is a fundamental problem in data structures. The paper uses a geometric view of the problem, which suggests that it may belong to the computational geometry (cs.CG) sub-category. The paper also uses techniques from information theory and machine learning, which suggests that it may belong to the information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper presents a new algorithm for the problem, which suggests that it may belong to the data structures (cs.DS) sub-category. Finally, the paper uses probabilistic and combinatorial arguments, which suggests that it may belong to the discrete mathematics (cs.DM) sub-category.
